1import SwiftUI
     2import AVFoundation
     3import UserNotifications
     4import Photos
     5import os.log
     6
     7private let permissionsLogger = Logger(subsystem: "app.vaultaire.ios", category: "Permissions")
     8
     9struct PermissionsView: View {
    10    let onContinue: () -> Void
    11
    12    @State private var notificationStatus: PermissionStatus = .notDetermined
    13    @State private var cameraStatus: PermissionStatus = .notDetermined
    14    @State private var photoStatus: PermissionStatus = .notDetermined
    15
    16    enum PermissionStatus {
    17        case notDetermined, granted, denied
    18    }
    19
    20    var body: some View {
    21        VStack(spacing: 32) {
    22            Spacer()
    23
    24            Image(systemName: "checkmark.shield.fill")
    25                .font(.system(size: 56))
    26                .foregroundStyle(.tint)
    27
    28            Text("Enable Permissions")
    29                .font(.title)
    30                .fontWeight(.bold)
    31
    32            Text("Vaultaire works best with these permissions. You can change them anytime in Settings.")
    33                .font(.subheadline)
    34                .foregroundStyle(.vaultSecondaryText)
    35                .multilineTextAlignment(.center)
    36                .lineLimit(nil)
    37                .padding(.horizontal, 24)
    38
    39            VStack(spacing: 16) {
    40                permissionRow(
    41                    icon: "bell.fill",
    42                    title: "Notifications",
    43                    description: "Know when backups and imports finish",
    44                    status: notificationStatus,
    45                    action: requestNotifications
    46                )
    47
    48                permissionRow(
    49                    icon: "camera.fill",
    50                    title: "Camera",
    51                    description: "Capture photos directly into your vault",
    52                    status: cameraStatus,
    53                    action: requestCamera
    54                )
    55
    56                permissionRow(
    57                    icon: "photo.fill",
    58                    title: "Photos",
    59                    description: "Import existing photos and videos",
    60                    status: photoStatus,
    61                    action: requestPhotos
    62                )
    63            }
    64            .padding(.horizontal, 24)
    65
    66            Spacer()
    67
    68            Button(action: onContinue) {
    69                Text("Continue")
    70                    .font(.headline)
    71                    .frame(maxWidth: .infinity)
    72                    .padding()
    73            }
    74            .vaultProminentButtonStyle()
    75            .padding(.horizontal, 32)
    76            .padding(.bottom, 24)
    77            .accessibilityIdentifier("permissions_continue")
    78        }
    79        .background(Color.vaultBackground.ignoresSafeArea())
    80        .task {
    81            await checkCurrentStatuses()
    82        }
    83    }
    84
    85    // MARK: - Views
    86
    87    private func permissionRow(
    88        icon: String,
    89        title: String,
    90        description: String,
    91        status: PermissionStatus,
    92        action: @escaping () async -> Void
    93    ) -> some View {
    94        HStack(spacing: 16) {
    95            Image(systemName: icon)
    96                .font(.title2)
    97                .foregroundStyle(.tint)
    98                .frame(width: 32)
    99
   100            VStack(alignment: .leading, spacing: 2) {
   101                Text(title)
   102                    .font(.headline)
   103                Text(description)
   104                    .font(.caption)
   105                    .foregroundStyle(.vaultSecondaryText)
   106                    .fixedSize(horizontal: false, vertical: true)
   107            }
   108
   109            Spacer()
   110
   111            switch status {
   112            case .notDetermined:
   113                Button("Allow") {
   114                    Task { await action() }
   115                }
   116                .buttonStyle(.borderedProminent)
   117                .controlSize(.small)
   118            case .granted:
   119                Image(systemName: "checkmark.circle.fill")
   120                    .foregroundStyle(.green)
   121                    .font(.title3)
   122            case .denied:
   123                Image(systemName: "xmark.circle.fill")
   124                    .foregroundStyle(.vaultSecondaryText)
   125                    .font(.title3)
   126            }
   127        }
   128        .padding()
   129        .vaultGlassBackground(cornerRadius: 12)
   130    }
   131
   132    // MARK: - Permission Requests
   133
   134    private func checkCurrentStatuses() async {
   135        async let notifSettings = UNUserNotificationCenter.current().notificationSettings()
   136        let cameraAuth = AVCaptureDevice.authorizationStatus(for: .video)
   137        let photoAuth = PHPhotoLibrary.authorizationStatus()
   138
   139        let settings = await notifSettings
   140        await MainActor.run {
   141            switch settings.authorizationStatus {
   142            case .authorized, .provisional: notificationStatus = .granted
   143            case .denied: notificationStatus = .denied
   144            default: notificationStatus = .notDetermined
   145            }
   146
   147            switch cameraAuth {
   148            case .authorized: cameraStatus = .granted
   149            case .denied, .restricted: cameraStatus = .denied
   150            default: cameraStatus = .notDetermined
   151            }
   152
   153            switch photoAuth {
   154            case .authorized, .limited: photoStatus = .granted
   155            case .denied, .restricted: photoStatus = .denied
   156            default: photoStatus = .notDetermined
   157            }
   158        }
   159    }
   160
   161    private func requestNotifications() async {
   162        do {
   163            let granted = try await UNUserNotificationCenter.current()
   164                .requestAuthorization(options: [.alert, .sound])
   165            permissionsLogger.info("Notification permission: \(granted)")
   166            await MainActor.run {
   167                notificationStatus = granted ? .granted : .denied
   168            }
   169        } catch {
   170            permissionsLogger.error("Notification request failed: \(error.localizedDescription)")
   171            await MainActor.run { notificationStatus = .denied }
   172        }
   173    }
   174
   175    private func requestCamera() async {
   176        let granted = await AVCaptureDevice.requestAccess(for: .video)
   177        permissionsLogger.info("Camera permission: \(granted)")
   178        await MainActor.run {
   179            cameraStatus = granted ? .granted : .denied
   180        }
   181    }
   182
   183    private func requestPhotos() async {
   184        let status = PHPhotoLibrary.authorizationStatus(for: .readWrite)
   185        if status == .notDetermined {
   186            PHPhotoLibrary.requestAuthorization(for: .readWrite) { newStatus in
   187                DispatchQueue.main.async {
   188                    switch newStatus {
   189                    case .authorized, .limited:
   190                        self.photoStatus = .granted
   191                    case .denied, .restricted:
   192                        self.photoStatus = .denied
   193                    default:
   194                        self.photoStatus = .notDetermined
   195                    }
   196                }
   197            }
   198        } else {
   199            await MainActor.run {
   200                switch status {
   201                case .authorized, .limited:
   202                    photoStatus = .granted
   203                case .denied, .restricted:
   204                    photoStatus = .denied
   205                default:
   206                    photoStatus = .notDetermined
   207                }
   208            }
   209        }
   210    }
   211}
   212
   213#Preview {
   214    PermissionsView(onContinue: {
   215        // No-op: preview stub
   216    })
   217}

   115/// A 5x5 dot grid with an animated path showing a pattern being drawn.
   116private struct PatternDemoGrid: View {
   117    let animatePattern: Bool
   118
   119    private let gridSize = 5
   120    private let dotSize: CGFloat = 10
   121    private let gridWidth: CGFloat = 200
   122
   123    // Highlighted dots (row, col) representing the demo pattern path
   124    private let highlightedDots: [(Int, Int)] = [(0, 0), (1, 1), (2, 2), (3, 3), (3, 4), (4, 4)]
   125
   126    var body: some View {
   127        ZStack {
   128            // Draw all dots
   129            ForEach(0..<gridSize, id: \.self) { row in
   130                ForEach(0..<gridSize, id: \.self) { col in
   131                    let isHighlighted = highlightedDots.contains { $0.0 == row && $0.1 == col }
   132                    Circle()
   133                        .fill(isHighlighted && animatePattern
   134                              ? Color.accentColor
   135                              : Color.vaultSecondaryText.opacity(0.3))
   136                        .frame(width: dotSize, height: dotSize)
   137                        .scaleEffect(isHighlighted && animatePattern ? 1.4 : 1.0)
   138                        .shadow(color: isHighlighted && animatePattern
   139                                ? Color.accentColor.opacity(0.5) : .clear,
   140                                radius: 8)
   141                        .position(dotPosition(row: row, col: col))
   142                }
   143            }
   144
   145            // Path lines
   146            if animatePattern {
   147                Path { path in
   148                    for (i, dot) in highlightedDots.enumerated() {
   149                        let pos = dotPosition(row: dot.0, col: dot.1)
   150                        if i == 0 {
   151                            path.move(to: pos)
   152                        } else {
   153                            path.addLine(to: pos)
   154                        }
   155                    }
   156                }
   157                .trim(from: 0, to: animatePattern ? 1 : 0)
   158                .stroke(Color.accentColor.opacity(0.6), style: StrokeStyle(lineWidth: 3, lineCap: .round, lineJoin: .round))
   159            }
   160
   161            // "Vault unlocked" badge at bottom
   162            if animatePattern {
   163                HStack(spacing: 8) {
   164                    Image(systemName: "lock.open.fill")
   165                        .font(.subheadline)
   166                        .foregroundStyle(.green)
   167
   168                    Text("Vault unlocked")
   169                        .font(.caption)
   170                        .fontWeight(.semibold)
   171                        .foregroundStyle(.green)
   172                }
   173                .padding(.horizontal, 16)
   174                .padding(.vertical, 10)
   175                .vaultGlassBackground(cornerRadius: 10)
   176                .offset(y: gridWidth / 2 + 30)
   177                .transition(.move(edge: .bottom).combined(with: .opacity))
   178            }
   179        }
   180        .frame(width: gridWidth, height: gridWidth)
   181    }
   182
   183    private func dotPosition(row: Int, col: Int) -> CGPoint {
   184        let spacing = gridWidth / CGFloat(gridSize - 1)
   185        return CGPoint(x: CGFloat(col) * spacing, y: CGFloat(row) * spacing)
   186    }
   187}

   357/// A 5x5 dot grid with a red duress pattern path.
   358private struct DuressPatternGrid: View {
   359    let animatePulse: Bool
   360
   361    private let gridSize = 5
   362    private let dotSize: CGFloat = 10
   363    private let gridSpan: CGFloat = 160   // distance between outermost dots
   364    private let circleSize: CGFloat = 200 // background circle diameter
   365
   366    // Duress pattern: Z-shape with direction changes
   367    private let highlightedDots: [(Int, Int)] = [(0, 0), (0, 2), (2, 2), (4, 0), (4, 2)]
   368
   369    var body: some View {
   370        ZStack {
   371            // Glow behind grid
   372            Circle()
   373                .fill(Color.red.opacity(0.06))
   374                .frame(width: circleSize, height: circleSize)
   375
   376            // Draw all dots
   377            ForEach(0..<gridSize, id: \.self) { row in
   378                ForEach(0..<gridSize, id: \.self) { col in
   379                    let isHighlighted = highlightedDots.contains { $0.0 == row && $0.1 == col }
   380                    Circle()
   381                        .fill(isHighlighted
   382                              ? Color.red
   383                              : Color.vaultSecondaryText.opacity(0.3))
   384                        .frame(width: dotSize, height: dotSize)
   385                        .scaleEffect(isHighlighted ? 1.4 : 1.0)
   386                        .shadow(color: isHighlighted
   387                                ? Color.red.opacity(animatePulse ? 0.5 : 0.2) : .clear,
   388                                radius: isHighlighted ? 8 : 0)
   389                        .position(dotPosition(row: row, col: col))
   390                }
   391            }
   392
   393            // Path lines connecting highlighted dots
   394            Path { path in
   395                for (i, dot) in highlightedDots.enumerated() {
   396                    let pos = dotPosition(row: dot.0, col: dot.1)
   397                    if i == 0 {
   398                        path.move(to: pos)
   399                    } else {
   400                        path.addLine(to: pos)
   401                    }
   402                }
   403            }
   404            .stroke(Color.red.opacity(0.5), style: StrokeStyle(lineWidth: 3, lineCap: .round, lineJoin: .round))
   405        }
   406        .frame(width: circleSize, height: circleSize)
   407    }
   408
   409    private func dotPosition(row: Int, col: Int) -> CGPoint {
   410        let spacing = gridSpan / CGFloat(gridSize - 1)
   411        let inset = (circleSize - gridSpan) / 2
   412        return CGPoint(x: inset + CGFloat(col) * spacing, y: inset + CGFloat(row) * spacing)
   413    }
   414}
